Interface ProcessingSort<X>

Type Parameters:
X - the underlying type.
All Superinterfaces:
AutoCloseable, Sort<X>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BubbleSort, BucketSort, ClassicSort, ClassificationSorter, HeapSort, InsertionSort, InsertionSortComparator, InsertionSortOpt, IntroSort, LSDStringSort, MergeSort, MergeSortBasic, MSDStringSort, QuickSort, QuickSort_3way, QuickSort_Basic, QuickSort_DualPivot, QuickSort_Exp, RandomSort, SelectionSort, ShellSort, SortWithComparableHelper, SortWithHelper, SortWithHelperAndAdditionalMemory, TimSort
public interface ProcessingSort<X> extends Sort<X>
Interface ProcessingSort. This interface defines the behavior of a sort with pre/post-processing. Note that the underlying type X is not required to be Comparable.
